---
// src/pages/privacy-policy.astro
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <div class="privacy-container">
    <div class="policy-hero-card">
      <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="policy-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="last-updated">Last Updated: 15th January 2025 · Version 2.0</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Intro Card -->
    <section class="policy-section intro-card">
      <h2>1. Overview & Acceptance</h2>
      <p>
        Hari Moradiya is the licensed owner of the application **Android TV Remote** ("Application"). We place our highest value on your trust and put top priority on protecting your Personal Information. This privacy policy ("Policy") explains how we will collect, use, share and process data.
      </p>
      <p>
        For the purpose of this Privacy Policy, "You" or "User" shall mean any natural or legal person who uses the Application, and "We", "Us", "Our", or "Company" shall mean Hari Moradiya.
      </p>
      <p>
        By accepting this Policy, you understand and agree to the collection, use, sharing and processing of your Personal Information. This Policy applies to all current and former visitors, users and others who access this Application.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Table of Contents -->
    <section class="policy-section toc-card">
      <h2>Table of Contents</h2>
      <ol class="toc-list">
        <li>Scope of this Policy</li>
        <li>Types of Information</li>
        <li>What Information is Collected?</li>
        <li>How is your Information Used?</li>
        <li>Who Will We Share this Information With?</li>
        <li>Data Portability</li>
        <li>How Do We Protect Your Information?</li>
        <li>How Can You Correct Inaccuracies?</li>
        <li>Your Duties</li>
        <li>Children's Privacy</li>
        <li>Indemnity</li>
        <li>Limitation of Liability</li>
        <li>Applicability of the Terms of Use</li>
        <li>Grievance Redressal Mechanism</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <!-- Scope -->
    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>2. Scope of this Policy</h2>
      <p>
        This Policy is an electronic record in the form of an electronic contract formed under the applicable law. This Policy does not require any physical, electronic or digital signature.
      </p>
      <p>
        This Policy describes the types of information we collect, why and how we use it, with whom we share it, and the choices you can make about our use of the information. We also describe the measures we take to protect the security of your information and how you can contact us about our privacy practices.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Types of Info -->
    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>3. Types of Information</h2>
      <p>We may collect, store and process Personal, Non-Personal and other third-party information.</p>
      
      <h3>3.1 Personal Information</h3>
      <p>
        Personal Information means any information that may be used to identify an individual, including but not limited to names, physical address, telephone number, email address, or financial information. We limit the collection of Personal Information to that which is necessary for its intended purpose.
      </p>

      <h3>3.2 Non-Personal Information</h3>
      <p>
        Non-personal information includes your device type, previously visited URLs, Internet Service Provider (ISP), television-related information (TV brand, model number), operating systems, and IP addresses.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Data Collection -->
    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>4. What Information is Collected?</h2>
      <p>
        For a better experience while using our Application, we may collect Non-Personal Information including device type, unique identifiers (such as iOS Advertising ID), carrier, and other related information through mobile SDKs. This data may be shared with third parties for advertising, attribution, analytics and research purposes (including Google AdMob and Google Firebase).
      </p>
      
      <h3>4.1 Log Data</h3>
      <p>
        When you use our Application, if any errors occur, we may collect data and information ("Log Data") through third-party products. This may include your device's IP address, device name, operating system version, app configuration, timestamp of usage, key presses, button presses, device connection success/failures, crash analytics data, and details about your television (brand, model, OS version).
      </p>

      <h3>4.2 Consent Withdrawal & Retention</h3>
      <p>
        You have the right to withdraw consent at any point by contacting our Consent Manager at **harimoradiya123@gmail.com**. Upon withdrawal, we shall erase all Personal Data provided by you, unless retention is required by law.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Data Use -->
    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>5. How is your Information Used?</h2>
      <p>
        We use information to provide personalized features, comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, enforce our agreements, and improve the Application by analysing how users interact with it.
      </p>
      <p>
        To provide enhanced functionality, we may leverage technologies such as regex parsing, template matching, artificial intelligence (AI), and machine learning (ML). We use service data for these technologies only to improve algorithm accuracy using anonymized and aggregated data.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Security & Protection -->
    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>6. How Do We Protect Your Information?</h2>
      <p>
        Our Application has stringent security measures in place to protect against loss, misuse, and alteration of information. Secure server software (SSL) encrypts all information before it is transmitted.
      </p>
      <p>
        Although we endeavour to safeguard your personally identifiable information, transmissions made over the internet cannot be made absolutely secure. By using this Application, you agree that we will have no liability for disclosure of your information due to errors in transmission or unauthorized acts of third parties.
      </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Grievance Redressal -->
    <section class="policy-section contact-card">
      <h2>7. Grievance Redressal Mechanism</h2>
      <p>
        In accordance with the Digital Personal Data Protection Act, 2023 and the Information Technology Act, 2000, the contact details for concerns are provided below.
      </p>

      <div class="contact-details-box">
        <p><strong>Name:</strong> Hari Moradiya</p>
        <p><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:harimoradiya123@gmail.com">harimoradiya123@gmail.com</a></p>
      </div>

      <p>
        If you wish to make a complaint regarding any violation of the provisions of this Policy, you may send a written complaint to the email above, who shall redress the complaint in accordance with the provisions of the Digital Personal Data Protection Act, 2023.
      </p>
    </section>
  </div>

  <style>
    .privacy-container {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      display: flex;
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 2rem;
      padding-top: 1rem;
    }

    /* Hero Card */
    .policy-hero-card {
      background: var(--bg-surface-glass);
      backdrop-filter: blur(var(--glass-blur));
      -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(var(--glass-blur));
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-lg);
      border-radius: 32px;
      padding: 3rem 2.5rem;
      position: relative;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--primary);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.15em;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
      display: block;
    }

    .policy-title {
      font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 3rem);
      font-weight: 800;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    }

    .last-updated {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      font-weight: 500;
    }

    /* Policy Sections */
    .policy-section {
      background: var(--bg-surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      border-radius: var(--card-radius);
      padding: 2.25rem;
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-sm);
      transition: all 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1);
    }

    .policy-section:hover {
      box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
      border-color: var(--primary);
    }

    .intro-card {
      border-left: 5px solid var(--primary);
    }

    .policy-section h2 {
      font-size: 1.4rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
      letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    }

    .policy-section h3 {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin: 1.5rem 0 0.5rem 0;
    }

    .policy-section p {
      font-size: 0.975rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      line-height: 1.6;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    .policy-section p:last-child {
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    /* TOC List */
    .toc-list {
      padding-left: 1.25rem;
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 0.75rem;
      color: var(--text-secondary);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .toc-list li {
      line-height: 1.4;
    }

    /* Contact Card */
    .contact-card {
      border-left: 5px solid var(--primary);
    }

    .contact-details-box {
      background: var(--bg-base);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
      padding: 1.5rem;
      border-radius: 12px;
      margin: 1.25rem 0;
    }

    .contact-details-box p {
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .contact-details-box p:last-child {
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }

    .contact-details-box a {
      color: var(--primary);
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    .contact-details-box a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    /* Responsive adjustments */
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .policy-hero-card {
        padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
      }

      .policy-section {
        padding: 1.5rem;
      }

      .toc-list {
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      }
    }
  </style>
</Layout>